# Tailwind CSS Guidelines

## Configuration
- [tailwind.config.js](mdc:tailwind.config.js) - Tailwind configuration for content paths and theme customization
- [.postcssrc.json](mdc:.postcssrc.json) - PostCSS configuration for Tailwind
- [src/styles.css](mdc:src/styles.css) - Global styles and Tailwind imports

## Best Practices
- Use Tailwind utility classes directly in templates
- Follow mobile-first responsive design
- Use @apply for repeated utility combinations
- Keep custom styles minimal and use Tailwind's built-in utilities

## Component Styling
- Use Tailwind classes in [app.html](mdc:src/app/app.html) and component templates
- Avoid writing custom CSS when possible
- Use Tailwind's responsive prefixes (sm:, md:, lg:, xl:)
- Leverage Tailwind's dark mode support

## Performance
- Tailwind automatically purges unused styles in production
- Keep utility class combinations minimal
- Use @layer to organize custom styles
- Follow Tailwind's performance optimization guidelines

## Common Patterns
- Use flex and grid utilities for layouts
- Utilize Tailwind's spacing scale
- Use color palette consistently
- Implement responsive designs using breakpoint prefixes



